@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<div class="gridHeader">
  <div class="header">
    <ul class="menu">
      <li><a href='/'>HOME</a></li>
      <li><a href='/restaurants'>FOOD</a></li>
      <li><a href='/hikes'>HIKES</a></li>
      <li><a href='/login/new'>LOGIN</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="grid">

  <div class="container">
    <h2>Where to hike before and after surfing (or instead?!)</h2>
    <hr>

    <div class="restaurants">
      <div class="gridRest">
        <figure class="guide gridBoxRest">
        <h3>Shortsands Beach :: Neahkahnie Mtn</h3>
          <p>Oregon Coast Hwy, Nehalem, OR 97131</p>
          <img src="../img/woman.jpg" alt="burger" width="600px">
          <img src="../img/ShortNeah.png" alt="map from beach to restaurant" width="600px">
          <p>distance: 6.4 mile | elevation: 2,070 feet</p>
          <p>Oregon Coast Trail to Neahkahnie Mountain is a 6.4 mile moderately trafficked out and back trail located near Nehalem, Oregon that features beautiful wild flowers and is rated as moderate. The trail offers a number of activity options and is best used from March until November. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.</p>
        </figure>
        <figure class="guide gridBoxRest">
          <h3>Pacific City :: Cascade Head Trail</h3>
          <p>N 3 Rocks Rd, Otis, OR 97368</p>
          <img src="../img/hiker.jpg" alt="hummus" width="600px">
          <img src="../img/PacificCascade.png" alt="map from beach to restaurant" width="600px">
          <p>distance: 6.3 mile | elevation: 1,381 feet</p>
          <p>Cascade Head Trail is a 6.3 mile moderately trafficked out and back trail located near Otis, Oregon that features a river and is rated as moderate. The trail offers a number of activity options and is best used from March until October.
          </figure>
        <figure class="guide gridBoxRest">
        <h3>Indian Beach :: Clatsop Loop Trail</h3>
          <p>84318 Ecola Park Road, Seaside, OR 97110</p>
          <img src="../img/hiker2.jpg" alt="fish and chips" width="600px">
          <img src="../img/IndianClatsop.png" alt="map from beach to restaurant" width="600px">
          <p>distance: 2.8 miles | elevation: 784 feet</p>
          <p>Clatsop Loop Trail from Indian Beach is a 2.8 mile moderately trafficked loop trail located near Cannon Beach, Oregon that features beautiful wild flowers and is rated as moderate. The trail offers a number of activity options and is accessible year-round. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.</p>
        </figure
        <hr>
        <div class= "footerRest">
          <h5>See what others are recommending or add a new hike:</h5>
          <br>
          <button><a href='/hikes/new'>Add a new hike</a></button>
          <br>

          @if (@Model.Count == 0)
          {
            <h3>No hikes have been added yet!</h3>
          }
          @foreach (var hike in Model)
          {
            <h3>@hike._hikeName</h3>
            <p>@hike._hikeAddress
            || @hike._hikeType</p>
            <p>@hike._hikeDescription</p>
            <hr>
          }

          <br>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="footer">
    <p>Â© 2019 ZAMN. All rights reserved.</p>
  </div>
</div>
